inn1.comm: pitches outside leg stump, he's late on the shot, brushes the pad and they get a leg bye first ball up
pitches outside off stump and no shot offered
lands outside leg stump, swings in, he hops and tucks it fine
swings and gets some good carry, except its pitched outside leg stump and gives Boucher some work to do behind the stumps, nevertheless Steyn will be excited
pitches fullish outside off stump and draws a loose shot
138.4ks, back of a length and dabbed toward cover
thats a loose ball, pitched up wide and Warner gets a chance to free the arms, so he reaches out and sends that screaming past cover for boundary number one
beauty to start off with, pitches on a length and deviates past the bat as Marsh plays inside the line, neither front nor back
just back of a length and Marsh hops across to defend it back

hops across tentatively again, defending high on the bat, ball rolls into the off side and Marsh is away, but its Warner who is struggling and needs a full stretch of a dive to get home, had a direct hit come in he was a goner
pitches full and swings in, Warner gets across and clips to midwicket
142.3ks, hits a length, he gets across and knocks it for one
a loose shot, Marsh is looking to leave a wide delivery but doesn't manage to get the bat out the way in time and it slips the toe end and runs down to third man
pitches on the stumps and he gets behind to play it back to Steyn
142.3ks, pitches on a length and he again pats it back
pitches wider, tempting the drive, but he resists watchfully
pitches a foot outside off stump and straightens, Marsh comes forward gently and shoulders arms, a pretty confident leave that one
comes forward and pushes a fuller one straight to cover
143ks, again angling across well and so Marsh leaves it be
pitches in the slot and this one is lofted over mid-on, two fielders give chase, de Villiers slides near the ropes and throws the ball past Botha behind him, so a free run
good ball, hitting short of a length to draw a tentative push and a thick outside edge that runs between the slips and gully and down to third man for one
slants back in off a length and Warner gets to the pitch firmly, pushing a single into the covers, that is some positive running
similar delivery and Marsh pushes into the covers, much more gently
straighter delivery and he shuffles and dabs it toward midwicket

tip and run from Warner, getting across and tucking a good moving deliver to the on side and setting off, he's struggling but stretches out the bat to just beat the direct flick from the midwicket fielder

more aggression from Warner, who drags a length delivery from outside off stump along the ground just wide of midwicket, not a short delivery and thus a premeditated shot, though not middled by any measure
pitches on off stump and he gets in line to defend it back
stunning shot! Steyn holds back the length marginally and Warner just pulls that over midwicket for six, that was smacked right off the middle of the bat, what batspeed
now he goes to the off side, reaching out and steering a full and wider delivery between the covers and point, its a long chase for Duminy and the ball just wins that race
well stopped Duminy, that had four written all over it! Warner again comes onto the front foot and pummels the ball hard but Duminy flings himself around and stops
slower ball outside off stump, too full and Warner again gives it a thump, but Duminy dives at cover and takes some pace off the ball, so just a single to Warner
good running, just tapped into the off side and they set off rapidly
nips back in off a short length, Marsh hops up and deflects to third man
pitches it up and Warner thumps it hard, but Duminy intercepts again
fractionally short of a length and Warner goes for a short-arm pull, but the ball is not on for that sort of shot and he ends up dragging it to midwicket
pitches fuller and he swings the bat at it, just clubbing over Botha at mid-off, not timed from Warner but he does pick it over the infield, a few more to his name
a touch shot, just whipping it from off stump, but to Amla at midwicket
short and a couple feet outside off stump, Warner reaches out and clangs it in the air over backward point and sprints back for a couple, he's not looking to hang around
short of a length, 139ks, he whips it away for a single past midwicket
full outside off stump, he pushes on the rise but point dives and saves
pitches just outside leg and straightens, hits the flap, can't be out
pitches full and straighter, well on-driven but Albie dives across to stop
hits a length and he keeps the last ball out for a single, dabbed gently
pitches on a length and thats pushed into the off side for one
Shibby! Warner is looking to beat each delivery to a pulp, this one pitches on a length just outside off stump and he swings it over mid-on for a boundary
nips in off a length and he falls forward as he pushes it to cover
pitches short of a length and he scoops it over midwicket with the angle
just back of a length and punched off the back foot to point
much, much fuller and he jams the bat on it, getting a single to mid-on
what placement! Warner short-arm jabs a length delivery, not timed well but the ball just evades mid-on and races away to the boundary, what a guy, and the 50 is up too
130ks, much fuller outside off and he pushes straight to cover
113ks, slower delivery, turned from middle and off to midwicket
ooh, turned off the pads just wide of mid-on, a loose shot that
pitches on leg, swings in, Warner punches past McKenzie at midwicket
pitches well outside leg stump, turned off the pads for a single
tries one of those cute dabbed singles, but mistimes it and slip fields
pitches on a length and he pushes that one straight to the cover fielder
a lovely delivery, 130ks but moving off the upright seam to bat the bat as a clueless Marsh pushes at it away from the body, that ball gently wobbled to Boucher
comes onto the front foot and pushes a single down to mid-on
a thick edge off Warner's bat this time, as he flashes it at one pitched up outside off stump, gets a single down to third man so its Marsh who's back on strike
short of a length and Marsh looks awkward as he fends it to point
a flat-batted punch straight down the ground, he wanted to pull it squarer but the length wasn't on, Kallis misfields in his followthrough but no chance of a single
clubs a fuller delivery, Steyn runs to his left at mid-off and dives to save runs
pitched up and that one is well on-driven, except it cant beat mid-on
whats this? Marsh has pierced the off side, and with a rather lovely shot too, that one pitched marginally full outside off stump and Marsh struck it on the rise for four
hits a length and now he rotates the strike with a dab to the off side
thats a wide, sliding down the pads, no contact from Warner, Boucher takes
comes forward and drives on the rise to mid-off, where Steyn tumbles
pitches on a length, middle and off, Warner wants a run but his attempt to shuffle across the sticks and rotate a single doesn't work, the ball dribbles down the track
nips in off a length to tuck up Warner, who hops and deflects it fine for one
ah, another one beats Marsh, who continues to flirt outside off stump, that pitched on the seam and wobbled away from the bat as Marsh went fishing, well bowled
gets some room and angles the bat on it, chopping just past gully
well bowled, on the stumps, no room to work with, Warner gets behind the ball and shape to knock it to the on side but he mistimes it back to Ntini
now its a full toss, which Warner cannot put past a diving JP Duminy at cover, so he has to stay on 49, much to the SCG's displeasure, they are backing the local boy
slower delivery on the stumps, cramping Marsh, who falls forward
hops up and turns that off the hips past midwicket for a single, to cheer!
dragged in short around off stump, Warner goes for a swing and misses, drawing boos from the SCG
now he gets to fifty, shuffling and turning the ball off his pads past square leg, there is some loud cheer from Warner's home crowd as he raises his maiden ODI half-century in his second match
pitches full, Marsh dabs it to extra cover, who is slow to react
change of pace but too straight and Warner drives to mid-on for one
108.6ks, back of a length and cracked off the back foot to cover
fuller, pitching outside leg stump and coming in, Warner pushes it back to Albie, cramped for room on the attempted on-drive past midwicket
now he gets him away, turning the ball off his pads down to fine leg
131.6ks, lands on middle and off and Marsh defends
straight again, off a shorter length, whipped to Duminy at deep midwicket
makes room and skips out, exposing all three sticks, the ball starts to follow Warner and he turns it just wide of midwicket for a single
makes room to smash that one over extra cover, one bounce and four
a cramped one-handed shot from Warner this time, trying to cut one just not there for that short of shot, ends up chopping to point and Marsh has to turn back and scamper back to his mark
hah! Kallis drops in an attempted bouncer but Warner collects from off stump and swats it over the infield for a flat six, thats a tremendous shot, and what placement
change of pace this time, sensibly, to draw a more conservative shot
hops back and knocks this one off the hips for an easy single
lands outside leg stump and Marsh works it off his pads to deep square
lands on a length and he turns it off the stumps to wide of midwicket
short-pitched on leg stump and hooked down to Steyn at fine leg
slower ball, pitches on leg stump, he wants to turn it fine but gets a leading edge that slowly pops up and drops short of Albie
another slower ball and another leading edge, this one well safe to cover
well bowled, Albie, pitching gently on the stumps and Warner defends
lands on leg stump, this time Warner gets one, driving past midwicket
pitches down leg stump and Marsh turns it down to deep square leg
well bowled, 140ks, a lovely yorker on leg stump, dug out in time

direct hit! Warner comes forward to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to the off side, Amla runs across from extra cover and nails a direct hit, the appeal is referred and it shows Warner just got his bat across the line
pitches on a length and Marsh pushes the ball to Amla at cover
better timing and placement from Marsh, who gets over a marginally fuller ball and drives it straight back past the stumps, this one mid-off cannot cut off
144ks, pitches just outside leg stump and Marsh plays it back
walks away to the sixth stump and goes inside-out down to long-off
111ks, pitches on leg stump and clipped aerially to midwicket
another dot ball as Marsh drives but cannot pierce cover or point
there's a shot! Marsh picks the shorter delivery and pulls it off one leg, over the infield and just over Duminy running back at deep midwicket, Albie thought he had his man but Marsh picked the spot
slower ball on the pads, turned through square for a couple more
hits a length on off stump and Marsh knocks it down toward mid-off
144ks, dug in short, Marsh opts to pull but takes his eyes off the ball and it strikes him on the pads well over the stumps, that one sort of skidded on to Marsh
pitches on the pads and he knocks that one into the on side
too straight again and he gets up to turn that one wide of square leg
again outside leg stump and flicked away for another easy single
sloppy, too much swing down leg stump, beating poor Boucher as well
you miss, I hit, mate! Full, fast and straight on the stumps, Warner swings across the stumps and cannot connect and Steyn flattens his leg stump, terminating a fun innings
beaten first ball, pushing at one pitched up outside off, well bowled
angling across and he bunts that from outside off stump to midwicket
hits a length and starts to straighten, Ponting punches it back to Albie
gets off the mark with a good shot, driven on the up past cover, no chance for the fielder to stop that one, wasn't a half-volley but Ponting collected on the rise
after the caress comes the club, as Ponting, in a flash, pulls that off the front foot, up and over midwicket for his second boundary in two balls
make it three in row, and note to self - do not bowl short to this man! Ponting gets across and paddle-pulls one drifting down leg stump up and over square leg
ah, gets a full toss but only manages to bunt a single down the ground
too straight and Ponting unfurls the vintage pull shot, its a good shot but Duminy covers plenty of ground from deep midwicket and dives to flick  the ball back
hits a length and he falls forward as he tries to tuck it away for one
slides down the pads, there's a faint noise, Boucher collects and asks
too straight and Marsh gets a faint tickle off the pads and its away
again he serves up on leg stump, 145ks, so Marsh flicks it away
good ball, short of a length on off stump and he defends
a good length this time, drawing Ponting forward, defending to cover
pitches on middle and angles away, Marsh gets across and pokes it away
comes forward and pushes the ball to the off side
comes onto the front foot and hammers the ball, very flat, to mid-off
fuller in length, hitting the seam, and he pushes it to point
comes back in this time but he counters with a firm on-drive for one
hits a length and this one is pushed straight to the fielders
tossed up gently, luring Ponting well forward, he drives into the off side
tossed up on middle and leg, some turn and Marsh defends to the off

quicker ball turns down the pads, Marsh goes for the sweep and gets well across the stumps, Boucher and Botha appeal but there was the faintest of inside edges as he placed it very fine around the corner for four
tossed up and he defends

smart work from Boucher, who collects the ball as it pitches and straightens to beat Marsh's attempted sweep to one outside off stump, Marsh drags his back leg just over the line and in a flash Boucher breaks the stumps, so Botha gets some success in his opening over
tossed up to bring Hussey forward, pushing toward cover
pitches wide, Ponting knocks the ball to point, where Albie slides well
tossed up wide and no shot offered, the umpire spreads his wings
comes onto the front foot and drives through the covers for one
tossed up, Ponting takes it on the half-volley and drives to extra cover
gently tossed up on off stump, Hussey pushes on the rise to the off
tossed up and turned wide of backward point for one more
fired in full and flat, and he uses his feet and drives it straight
short and pulled to deep midwicket, cracking shot there
much slower, tossed up on the stumps and Hussey defends
comes across and works this one away for a quick single
tossed up, Ponting steers it to Amla on the off and wants one, but nope
uses his feet and clips this one wide of the fielder for one
tossed up on a length, hint of turn, defended off the front foot to point
tossed up and he bunts a single down the ground
too much drift down leg stump and Hussey sweeps it away
smart running, dabbed away and they sprint off, beating the throw
serves up a low full toss which Hussey punches into the off side
tossed up and it drifts into the pads, Ponting turns it to midwicket
another easy single, turned off the pads between midwicket and mid-on
some turn there, away from middle and off, Hussey defends it back
just a tad too short and he punches it into the covers for a single
too short for sure and he rocks back to punch between cover and point
tossed up just outside off stump and pushed straight to point

well done, de Villiers! Botha tosses it up wider, drawing a flashy drive off the edge to backward point, where de Villiers runs across, collects, and returns a flat throw on top of the stumps to Boucher, Hussey has set off and turns back and dives but he is nowhere in the frame, that was really brilliant fielding
tossed up on off stump, Hussey comes across and turns to midwicket
pitches outside off stump and Ponting square-drives on the rise
pitches it up and Hussey drives on the up, finding the gap at cover for two
slower ball, 117ks, commits Hussey on the front foot and he adjusts well, playing it late and with soft hands, steering down to third man for a single
comes onto the front foot and drives out to the sweeper at deep cover
hits a length and he pushes that to the fielder
straighter delivery, flicked across the line but straight to midwicket
tossed up fine, Ponting paddles it around the corner to fine leg
flatter delivery which Hussey collects on the full and flicks across the line
what a simple dismissal, its gently tossed up and Ponting just plays across his pads to short midwicket, who stumbles a couple feet forward and accepts the offering, easy as can be
tossed up slowly again, Haddin pushes down the track
again he pushes it back and Botha gets across to stop the ball
clips this one to the on side where the fielding is decidedly sprightly
tossed up on off stump, turned with the spin down to mid-on
tossed up, some turn, Haddin works it uppishly to midwicket
comes out and turns it to midwicket, calling for the urgent single
slowly lobbed up outside off, drawing him forward in defence
slowly tossed up and this one is turned to the on side fielder
ah, well bowled, tossed up every so gently and that one is driven on the rise just over the head of extra cover
strides well forward and across the stumps to block this one back
a misfield from Duminy! The length forces Haddin back, he flicks across the line, Duminy moves across from midwicket but fumbles the collection, otherwise Hussey was gone for all money
tossed up and he works it across the line for one
tossed up and he plays it to the fielder
tossed up and gets him driving but he cannot beat cover
tosses it up, he comes out and turns the ball to the onside, sets off, again the nonstriker is struggling to make it but Boucher breaks the stumps just a frame too  late
tossed up and played out solidly
skips out and drills that very firmly back past the stumps
tossed up on the stumps and he defends
invites the drive with one tossed up too wide and Hussey reaches out to drive over extra cover for four
this one pitches on the stumps and turns fine, Hussey deflects it away
collects on the full and drives this down the ground to long-off
pushes him onto the back foot and he drives in the air toward mid-on
collects on the full and whips it across the line to midwicket for one
Haddin's gone, and Botha has a third! Tossed up, lures Haddin out of his crease, he drives it low and flat back to Botha, who holds it very well and then throws it up
tossed up, Hopes goes back and defends watchfully
again he pushes him back and across and he plays it back
tossed up, Hussey flicks from outside off, nearly to short midwicket
slides down the pads and that one is turned to square leg
opens the face and dabs that straight to the fielder
comes out and turns that wide of the fielder for a single
drives it back and Duminy dives across to stop off his own bowling
tossed up outside off stump and he drives this down to deep mid-off
slowly tossed up on the pads and he turns it right to midwicket
tossed up and defended
comes across and clips off the stumps to wide of midwicket
too straight this time and he works it off his pads past square leg
slower ball on middle and off, defended to the on side
slides down and he knocks it to the on side for one this time
a touch shorter and we see a rare back-foot shot, just wide of cover
full and swinging, well clipped but McKenzie flings around and stops
short of a length, tapped into the off side, sprints off, fielder collects and fires the throw but Hussey is just home safe
gets a wee bit of room and he runs it down to third man for one
pitches on off stump, driven loosely toward midwicket, who dives
back of a length on the stumps and he gets in line to defend
pitched up wider, Hopes reaches for it and drives on the rise through a diving cover fielder and gets four to his name, that was truly a powerful shot
good shot for one, tossed up and Hussey clips past midwicket in style
tossed up again and another flick, but Gibbs intercepts
lobbed up on the stumps and he drives that down the ground
comes out and gets the wrists into play, working wide of mid-on
flighted up, turns back in, batsman goes back and across
bit too wide on that occasion and Hopes drives into the covers for one
flat stuff, forcing Hopes back and he punches to the bowler
gently tossed up and Hopes drives it down toward mid-on
tossed up again, Duminy moves across to his right and cuts it off
and again, flighted up and he mistimes the drive to the fielder
now he breaks the shackles with a steered single into the off side
very well done, Duminy, tossed up on the stumps and turned to midwicket
flighted up gently on the stumps, Hopes plays it to midwicket
more lovely flight and dip and his flick is cut off by a diving midwicket
flighted up again and he clips the ball to the man at midwicket
a touch wider and he gets room to push the ball toward extra cover
comes onto the front foot and pushes the ball to point
gets his front foot out and turns the ball across his pad, beating mid-on
slowly tossed up outside off, Hussey nudges it down to short third man
comes forward and flicks it to midwicket, no chance of a run there
produces the sweep now, just getting enough on it to beat square leg
tossed up and defended
tossed up, flicked off the pads to Ntini at deep square leg
drives firmly off the front foot, Duminy misfields and allows one
short ball, Hopes moves back and pushes down the ground
full and flat, well bowled, clipped straight to midwicket

shout for leg before, the ball straightens down the leg stump and the batsman gets a leg bye, he was hit in front of about middle and leg, a very good shout, replays show it was turning down the stumps
tossed up and defended
tossed up again, gets well forward and struck outside the line
comes forward and pushes the ball back, another ambitious shout
slowly pitched up to tempt the drive, he goes for it and just beats short cover
goes for another drive and misses, well taken by Boucher
short and wide and carved out to Duminy at deep cover
now thats well played by Hopes, swiping across the line over midwicket
pitches on a drivable length and Hopes plays straight to cover
pitches very full again and he hits it very hard into the off side
tossed up on the stumps, turned from off stump to midwicket
tossed up and thats a very sturdy piece of defensive work
decides to clip this one but cannot beat midwicket
lunges forward and turns it just wide of the midwicket fielder
slides down leg stump for a wide, Boucher collects cleanly
tossed up on off stump, nudged toward square leg for one
plants the front pad in line and whips that away through midwicket
what a bad ball, a wide full toss and he can only slap out to deep cover
throws the bat at width but cannot beat backward point
pushes at another wider one, the attempted yorker, and opens the face to squeeze it down to third man for a welcome boundary to Australia
another attempted yorker, this one swinging down the pads, clipped fine
pitches on a length and he drives that toward point
shorter ball, sliding back with the angle, forced straight to backward point
tossed up on the stumps and he flicks it to deep midwicket
dances down the track and drives inside-out to deep cover
drives it back to Duminy's right, a fumble allows them one to mid-on
comes out, Duminy sees him and fires it in, he flicks and Gibbs dives
comes out and nudges that one down to de Villiers in the deep
gives him some room but he can only drive to McKenzie at extra cover
hah, he's missed a rank waist high full toss! Ntini slips it out and Hussey just does not pick it as he opens the face to steer it fine, makes no contact and back goes middle stump
from around the stumps, short of a length, and steered past point
overpitched and Hopes firmly drives through the covers for a single
angles in off a length, just defended in the off side and he sprints
swings back in to leg stump, Hopes makes room and on-drives one
great timing, thats pitched up and he punches it off the middle and picks the gap between covers and even a sprinting sweeper fails to cut it off, very pleasing stroke
dances down and swings across the line, just manages the toe end of the bat on the ball and drags it down into the midwicket region for a single
tossed up on a length and he defends it back watchfully
slides down the pads, Boucher collects
good shot, just kneels down and swings over mid-wicket for four
dragged on! Johnson dances down, making room, and swings and misses and gets a faint under edge that cannons back into the base of the stumps
and he gets off the mark immediately, tucking two past square leg
tosses it up wide, he reaches out and swings it past midwicket in style
pitches outside off stump and he flashes the drive through cover
slower ball on middle and leg, Hauritz shuffles and dabs it away
dragged in short outside off stump, Hopes fetches it and pulls to long-on
pitches it up, Hauritz makes room and tries to drive inside-out but finds Botha, stationed at cover, running backward to take a neat catch over his head
hits a length and he pokes at it, missing by not much, well bowled
slower ball, short of a length, steered just short of Gibbs at backward point
pitches full and Bracken pushes it into the covers for a quick single
full on the stumps, makes room and clips to Botha at midwicket
good stroke on the rise, punching the ball into the gap at extra cover
full in the slot, no room to work with, squeezed into the off side for one

oh well taken, Botha! Ntini gets another by pitching full down leg stump, getting the ball to swing in with the angle, Hopes chips it off the pads low in the air towards Botha, staying back on the circle, who then runs across and dives to hold a very sharp catch
ah, this one slides in and draws an inside edge back onto the flap as Bracken pushes tentatively at it, the ball then proceeds to deflect down toward gully
short of a length and he forces it off the back foot to backward point

whats happening here? Tait hops away toward square leg and drops the short delivery to the off side, Bracken sets off but there is no reaction from Tait, who is ball watching, suddenly both men are at one end and Tait had no chance to get back as the throw comes back to Botha on the bounce, who dislodges the stumps

inn2.comm: banged in short outside off stump and Amla drops his hands to allow it go
148.8ks, Amla hops up to cut and David Hussey dives up at point, intercepts it superbly and throws at the nonstriker's end, missing and Gibbs is safe

edged and dropped by Ponting, who clutches to his left side from second slip and fluffs what should have been Michael Hussey's chance a first slip, then he allows a couple to boot, so a lucky break for Amla ... that was well bowled, back of a length and deviating to draw and edge from a leaden-footed Amla but the bowler has been let down by his captain
pitches rather wide of the stumps
pitches outside off stump again and Amla steers a single away
ah, well done, pitches it up and beats a loose waft outside off stump

another drop! This one is by David Hussey at backward point, who falls forward to try and cup a loose thick outside edge from Gibbs' bat as the flings it a wide delivery, but the fielder fails to hold on .. my oh my what an opening over
hits a length and he keeps that one out
pitches on leg stump and curls back in, Amla tucks it to midwicket
pitches full to bring Amla forward, swings back and he pushes to cover
argh, more frustration for Australia as Amla drives without much footwork and gets an inside edge back past leg stump and Haddin for a fortuitous boundary
pitches full again and this time Amla pushes firmly to cover
full on the pads and delicately twirled down to deep square leg
150.9ks, short and a bit wide and Amla cuts straight to point
short and wide again and this time he laces it behind point for two
well bowled, the attempted yorker, full and swinging, Amla gets across and jams bat down on it, and then runs very well to scamper across the other end, well backed by Gibbs
another tailing yorker, 148ks, it so nearly snuck through but Gibbs dug it out to the on side and gets off the mark
short again, Amla rides the bounce and chops it in front of point for one
amazing shot that from Gibbs, who doesn't move around much, instead going back and chipping the ball, totally using the pace, over mid-on for a one-bounce four

pitches and comes in, Amla squirts it to the off side, sets off, Gibbs says where do you think you're going as two fielders converge, Amla has to retrace his steps and only survives because the throw was off the mark
too straight and Amla glances it off the pads down to fine leg
pitches outside leg, tails in, Gibbs pushes it back to Bracken
short of a length, again outside leg stump, turned to midwicket
starts to come out, Bracken sees him and holds back the length and all Gibbs can do is steer it to the off side off the front foot, that was well bowled
shorter this time and he gets the wrists into play, turning it fine
short, on the stumps, tucks Amla up, who has no room to make anything out of this and plays it back to Tait
pitched up, fast at 151ks, Amla goes for it, a wristy square-drive goes through vacant gully region
vintage Gibbsy, premedidates, steps down, meets Tait on the half volley, and lofts him over his head, one bounce for four, this was no power, just a chip
pitched up further, 153ks, Gibbs goes for a lofted cover-drive, but misses completely
another quick delivery, 153ks, pitched up, driven to cover
tries a bouncer, just outside off, Amla takes a half movement forward, drops his wrists, and sways out of the line
another typical Gibbs shot first up, this was wide and pitched up, and Gibbs opens the face and deliberately chips it over cover

Suicide! run-ut, Gibbs is beaten by the extra bounce, and sees Amla charging down even before he has recovered, takes one step down but realises there is no single in this as Warner is charging at it from cover. it's an easy chip from Warner and Amla is gone
Gibbsy is not affected meanwhile, a lovely cover-drive... another wide, pitched-up delivery, and caressed through the covers
pitched up outside off again, but Gibbs doesn't connect properly and plays straight to cover
on the pads, played to just wide of mid-on for a single
Kallis gets an inside edge first up, this is pitched up outside off, and Kallis looks for a drive without any foot movement. Lucky not to play this on, he will get a single too
straight, on the pads, but Gibbs can't beat the midwicket
slower ball, 117.8ks, it's on the pads, and Gibbs looks to paddle it but is early into the shot
a little shimmy down the track, Bracken pulls this one back, and Gibbs plays it back to the bowler
this is a touch loose, thrown across Gibbs this time, he looks to free his arms, but  plays aerially through gully region
accurate, pitched around leg, angling across towards off, played watchfully by Kallis
another accurate delivery on the stumps, and played back to the bowler
great use of the feet, backing away to leg stump, making room to loft that inside out and over extra cover for a big six to set the fans down in that stand alive
comes out again and pushes with one hand, the ball beats bat
charges down but Johnson slips in a yorker outside off stump which Gibbs cannot put away this time
slips in a short delivery this time to draw a leading edge from the bat as Gibbs jumps across his stumps, it pops up in the air but evades Johnson, running to his right
Haddin is having a tough time out there, failing to collect one that stays low and beats the bat and then doesn't carry properly to the wicketkeeper
smack, go fetch! Johnson drops fractionally short and Gibbs collects in style from outside off stump, bisecting two fielders on the leg side
starts off on a tidy length and commits Kallis onto the front foot, blocking
comes forward and drives, threading the gap at cover
back of a length this time and Kallis is concrete in defence
delicious shot, not a bad ball from Hopes but Kallis walks across his stumps, then flicks it superbly past midwicket for four
serves it up wide, Kallis square-drives, David Hussey dives to save runs
pitches full and Gibbs comes forward to defend it to the off side
ah lovely, pitches on the seam and goes on with the angle to square up Kallis, who pushes down the wrong line and the ball beats the outside edge
a gift-wrapped half-volley and he square-drives it with class for four
now that did not bounce! Johnson pitches shorter and the ball scoots across the turf, well underneath Kallis' bat as he flirts at it, and Haddin manages to stop it
fuller in length and Kallis mistimes the drive to the off side
134.8ks, back of a length and Kallis goes back to defend it
short down the stumps and he works it off the hips for a single
pitches on a good length and some very tidy defensive stuff from Kallis
a shimmy and Kallis clips extravagantly, but straight to midwicket
miscues another drive, this one a booming one to mid-off
pitches on leg and swings in, Kallis shuffles and flicks a single
pitches just outside off stump and he angles it to backward point
and he stays there, for now, because Hopes bowls a stump-to-stump delivery which Kallis has to defend down to backward point
slower ball, attempted yorker outside off stump, no shot offered
short of a length on leg stump and he muscles it to midwicket
short of a length outside off and he goes back to defend to cover
good bowling, pitches on middle and leg and curls away and Kallis gets right in line with the ball, pushing it back with a straight face
what is that? That slips out of Johnson's hands and flies well wide of Kallis at about shoulder length, surprising Kallis, then Haddin collects it well
goes to flick one outside leg stump but no bat, so leg byes
fun to watch, is Gibbs, who rides the bounce of a short delivery and paddle-pulls it over square leg for four, that was a controlled and confident shot
pitches on the stumps and he tries an on-drive, but mistimed
nips back in off the seam and Kallis defends to cover
slides down the stumps, he goes to pull but ball hits thigh pad
comes forward and drives down the ground, mid-off cuts it off

and Jacques Kallis joins the 10,000 club with that shot, just opening the face and coolly running it down to third man for a single, he jogs down the track and takes off his helmet to acknowledge the applause from the SCG, what a player he has been for South Africa!
innovative shot that from Gibbs, pushing forward and then at the last minute twirling the bat to send the ball racing away safely past Haddin and no chance for third man to cut it off
a loose shot, reaching out to drive and Kallis gets a thick outside edge well safe of the slips, Tait shakes his head and walks back to his mark
146.4ks, a late-swirling yorker going down leg stump, Kallis falls across and then clips the ball to midwicket
great shot from Gibbs, shimmying down and driving all along the grass, past extra cover, who only has to go and retrieve the ball from the ropes

well now, thats one of those shots which you just stand back and admire and say well played, mate! Again Gibbs comes down the track and this time just pushes the ball into that gap at extra cover for four more
expectedly, Tait drops it short and Gibbs miscues the cut to point
stands his ground and steers the ball wide of point to raise a great fifty
swings down the pads and he clips it behind square leg for one
pitches outside the line and slants down, Gibbs gets across and plays a paddle shot, misses out on the bat, they all appeal but it was doing too much
drives from the crease and misses, well taken by Haddin
comes forward and rolls the wrists, late, to pinch another past square leg
shorter delivery, not that wide but Gibbs gets on top of it and sends it screeching away behind point and even third man, covering good ground, cannot cut it off
a loose drive off the front foot this time, but safely in the air past point
gently tossed up and Kallis drives handsomely past extra cover
comes across and paddles this from off stump to short fine leg
gives it some air and Kallis squirts an outside edge wide of gully
goes back to cut and survives with an under edge onto his boot
floats it up wider and Kallis chases it with a square-drive behind point
tossed up on off stump, Gibbs gently turns it straight to square leg
pitches on a length and Kallis dabs it very late off the face of the bat
too straight and thats turned with the angle for one to deep square leg
pitches on a length, Kallis again glides it toward third man
it all looks rather easy at the moment, with Gibbs also running one fine
goes back and punches this one off the back foot into the covers
well played, Gibbs gets well across the stumps and paddles this from outside off down to deep square leg, where it is cut off by the sweeper
moves across and paddles, misses and the ball nearly hits leg stump, Haddin shuffles across and cannot connect cleanly so the ball deflects away
flighted down the pads and Gibbs runs it off away to fine leg for two
pitches and flights down leg stump, and thats wide
tossed up down the stumps, he gets across and misses the sweep
goes back and tries to run it fine but makes a mess
flighted up again and he connects with the sweep this time
tosses it up and draws a leading edge into the covers, well bowled
taps it to midwicket, sets off, there's confusion but all is well
pitches on the stumps and he turns it to midwicket, then sprints
dabs a short ball to the off side, sets off a few paces, Marsh collects and Kallis, who has to turn back, survives because the throw is astray
makes room and skips out, Johnson follows him cleverly, and Gibbs does well to remove the front leg and squirts an inside edge down to backward square leg
wonderful placement, clipping in the air past square leg
pitches outside leg stump and Kallis taps it to midwicket for one
finally Australia hold one, its just catching practice from Gibbs, not moving as he reaches out and plays it off the face of the bat smack to first slip, who cups it in front of his face

big shout from Hauritz, who flights it up outside the line and then beats Kallis as he shuffles across, they all go up in appeal and thats a very good call from the umpire Ian Gould, as replays show it pitched just outside the line
gets forward and pushes the away for a quick single
off the mark first ball, turning the ball off his stumps for one
turns it off the stumps to short fine leg, de Villiers says no thanks
flights it up wider to get Kallis coming forward, steering past point
a shot of twinkle-toed confidence early in his innings, just waltzing down and clipping with the turn, placing it over midwicket and there's no stopping that
very full just outside off and Kallis miscues the shot to midwicket
beaten! That pitches back of a length and goes on with the natural angle, staying a shade low to beat  the edge of the bat as Kallis pushes for it loosely, well bowled
133ks, on middle and leg and turned uppishly to midwicket
oh well played, Johnson drops it a tad shorter and in a flash Kallis scoops it off one leg, and into the yawning spaces behind square leg
much fuller outside off stump and punched into the covers, a sharp call for the single and the cover fielder misses the stumps
much better length this time and AB can only defend to cover
hits a length and stays low to scoot past the edge of the bat
comes forward and bisects the gap, runs hard for the second
comes onto the front foot and drives, ball stays low and rolls past
edged and Hussey takes another easy catch in front of his face! Bracken pitches full and angles it away to tempt the drive, AB chases it and gives a regulation edge to first slip
pitches outside off stump and no shot offered
banged in short and he pushes and misses, well bowled
short of a length outside off stump, Kallis clips it past midwicket
very, very full and wide and Kallis resists having a go, smartly
pitches on leg stump, he shuffles and turns it away to raise fifty
pitches full and wide and Duminy shoulders arms
slips up a full toss, Duminy does well to clip it past midwicket
full on middle and off, flicked with the swing straight to midwicket
138.4ks, short of a length and he defends it solidly
pitches on about leg stump and Kallis gets across, tucking it fine
shorter and he tries to flick it on the hop, but mistimes it back
well bowled, hits the upright seam and wobbles back in to beat Duminy
lures him forward with a fuller one and Duminy edges to gully
drives a full one again and this time cannot beat backward point
pitches short of a length and gets some extra bounce, Duminy pushes at it away from the body and misses, Haddin collects and appeals, then Bracken joins in, but the umpire is not interested
hits a good length and seams in and Kallis pushes to the off side
pitches and straightens and Duminy hops back to defend it
sees width and chases it, only to under-edge into the off side
short of a length and he drives into the covers off the back foot, there's a moment of hesitation between the batsmen before they eventually set off
goes back and plays the ball just wide of the fielders this time
lands on leg and curls in, Duminy counters with a nudge to the on side
gently flighted up and he dabs the ball away for one
tossed up and he plays it back
tries to open the face and dab it fine but mistimes it poorly
comes forward and knocks the ball toward midwicket for one
shuffles across and works the ball to midwicket, cant find the gap
gets across and steers the ball to short third man
pitches on the pads and another easy two to Kallis, clipped away
quicker ball, 129.3ks, Kallis cramped for room but expertly opens the face of the blade and guides the ball down to third man for one more to the total
hits a length and he plays this one out to the fielder
ah, close, hits a length and shaves away and Duminy dabs the ball at the last moment to short third man, who dives and fumbles and allows runs
gentle stuff on the stumps and pushed into the off side
not that short but Duminy pulls in front of square and beats the fielder
tossed up on a teasing line, Kallis pushes and edges to the off side
slows the pace, Kallis pushes to point and waves back Duminy
pushes forward and inside-edges off the pad to short fine leg
stays in his crease and works the ball away toward Bracken at point
works this one away but cannot beat the fielders

bowled em! This one is tossed up outside off and purchases a bit of turn from the rough, cramping Duminy as he goes for a cut, stays low and a faint inside edge disturb off stump and thats an ODI wicket for Hauritz for the first time since May 2003
pitches and shapes back in, Kallis on-drives the ball to midwicket
Tait strikes! Kallis throws it away with a poor back-foot shot, chasing a length ball from his crease and all he can succeed in doing is feather a thin edge to an ecstatic Haddin
146.3ks, short of a length and hit away to the off side first ball
fuller on off stump and pushed down to mid-on
hops forward and pushes the ball back, thats some tidy bowling
bangs it in and Boucher hops up to defend it back to Tait
tossed up wide, spins back in and McKenzie keeps bat tucked inside
uses his feet and works the ball into the on side for a couple
gets across and whips it from outside off stump to wide of mid-on
gently lobbed up on a length, he comes up and pushes it away
gets back and plays this one to the fielder
comes across and knocks the ball to the on side
hits a length and he can only defend that to the off side
very tidy stuff on top of off stump, defended to backward point
gets a wider one and steers it to Ponting, sliding at short cover
a tad fuller but still McKenzie fails to find the gap, driving to Ponting
at last he gets one, rising up and forcing the ball wide of point
pitches on off stump and straightens, on-driven down the ground
148.3ks, pitched up outside off and he leaves it be
hits a length on off stump, on the seam, and McKenzie defends
full and tailing back, hits the pads but clearly missing leg stump
full down the pads, brushes something and Haddin flings himself around to his left to pouch the ball, appeals for the catch and replays show it brushed the pads
banged in short, 150.1ks, McKenzie deflects it to square leg
short of a length and Boucher steers it down to third man for one
pitches on middle and off and he pushes the ball to midwicket
back of a length, cramps him and he plays the ball to point
gets a wider one and squirts it down to third man for one
fuller in length and he mistimes the drive to Ponting at cover
nips back in but he angles the face and steers one to third man
a much straighter delivery, which Boucher on-drives for a single

oh its all happening at the SCG! First Tait fires in a lovely late-swinging yorker that nearly snaps the batsman's toes, but it was missing leg stump, then he sets off for leg byes and gets sent back, the nonstriker stumbles, the throw misses, Boucher looks to have injured himself and he's on his knees with the umpire asking if all is well
another yorker, this one honing into off stump, Boucher just manages to squirt the bat down on the ball and inside-edges back past the stumps and wide of Haddin
full toss on the stumps and thats pushed straight to cover
hits a good length and he dabs the ball to backward point
another low full toss on the stumps, pushed to mid-on, who is quick
oversteps, pitches it full and wide, Boucher cannot connect well, Haddin runs in to collect and we have the first free hit of the match
full and wide, sliced to backward point, where David Hussey intercepts
pitches back of a length and Boucher defends to point
fuller in length and Boucher plays it back to Hopes
short of a length on middle and off and Boucher punches to midwicket
slips it in again, Boucher gets up and cannot time it well at all
too wide this time so Boucher cuts a single out to deep cover
nips back in off a length and he steers it toward backward point
full and low full toss outside off stump, squirted to cover
reaches out and squeezes it off the end of the bat, beating gully
pitches and stays low and he plays it off the back foot to third man
back of a length and he shuffles, working the ball away
ah, a loose edge as he feels for it and the ball drops in font of Haddin and first slip, that was a very poor shot and he's lucky it didn't carry
pitches full and wide and he drives on the up to Ponting at short cover
pitches and angles across McKenzie, who pokes it to backward point
walks into the shot and collects on the half-volley, pushing to cover
comes forward and defends the ball down to backward point
pitches outside leg stump, turned away to midwicket
walks down the track, dabs the ball to the leg side and carries on walking and Boucher has to shoo him back as Bracken harries across and collects the ball
jams in a yorker outside off stump, McKenzie hasn't a clue as he pokes at it, and thats another maiden from that man Bracken
tossed up and thats flicked away wide of square leg for one
tossed up gently and McKenzie paddles it from outside off to the deep
another swipe across the stumps, into the massive space at midwicket, looks to be headed to the boundary but Warner sprints across and slides superbly to cut it off
well played, going back and steering it wide of backward point
uses his feet and chips the ball wide of mid-on
skips down and swats it with an inside edge to deep square leg
good bowling, full on the stumps, with some swing, but equally well picked and pushed back past Bracken, then Boucher notices that mid-off is slow and runs
pitches in line and pushed back to the off side
goes down to slog sweep but cannot pierce midwicket
reaches out and steers the ball down to third man for one
gives him the charge and swings, but the ball stays low to beat him
hits a length and he pushes the ball down to extra cover
a boundary for McKenzie, whats this? Hauritz proposes, McKenzie makes room and drives inside-out over the covers, thats a shot the South Africans really enjoy
streaky one this time, running it off the face very loosely
drifts down the stumps and brushes away off Haddin's pads
skips out and hits this over the bowler's head, well struck shot
gets across and hits this out to Michael Hussey in the deep

lovely arm from that man Warner! Boucher skips out, collects on the full and flicks through midwicket, a well-struck shot that but then out of the blue comes Warner, huffing and puffing and collecting and throwing it back to Hauritz, who breaks the sticks with McKenzie, having been waved back, just short of the crease
tossed up, he gets across and bunts the ball to midwicket
goes fishing very first delivery and gets beaten by a whisker
short of a length and he gets up to steer the ball wide of point
backs away and slices the short ball flush between cover and point
served up on a length and Albie clears the front leg, gets to the pitch and smokes that handsomely over mid-on for four
the response is true fast bowler's, banged in short at 144.4ks to get Albie falling back on his haunches

and now its Tait's turn to drop a catch! Albie moves back to expose all three stick and then slices that from on top of middle and off, its in the air and running down to Tait, sprinting across from third man, who dives and cups it but then spills the chance to allow Albie a life
pitches full on the stumps, pushed back past mid-on and they hustle
147ks, on the stumps and defended back to Tait
hits a length, Boucher gets to the pitch and punches over Tait's head
well bowled yorker, which he somehow digs out to point
makes room and flat-bats it very firmly down to Marsh at mid-off
chases a low full toss and slices it off the edge wide of backward point
slower delivery, Albie makes room and just gets bat on it, steering it to the off side and setting off, a bit of hesitation but they cross as Tait fields and flings it back
full toss, hit nowhere but back to Bracken, who fields it well
gives him the charge but can only hit the ball to midwicket for one
crafty little slower ball, full on about off stump, Morkel clears the front leg and drives, getting a little inside edge back onto his boot, but scampers the single
lovely timing and placement from Boucher, using his feet to get over the attempted yorker, then improvising with a chipped flick between midwicket and mid-on
carves a low full toss to Hauritz at short third man, who fumbles and allows a single
pitches on off stump and Boucher pinches a single to extra cover
makes room and drives to extra cover, where Ponting tumbles and stops
quick yorker down leg stump, Boucher clears the toe and jams it out
pitches on the stumps and he plays it back to Tait
another yorker, this one two feet outside off stump to beat the bat
attempted yorker on off stump, again Morkel backs away and steers the ball toward third man and scampers off, Tait has over-stepped so another free hit
makes room, Tait pitches full, and Boucher drives it to extra cover
slips up a wide full toss and Bracken cuts it past point for one
whoa there, Albie! Once more he moves outside leg stump and goes for a cut, this time just scooping it over a leaping Marsh at point
pitches and slants into leg stump, Albie coolly tucks it for a single
fuller ball outside off and Boucher hits it back to Bracken
very full again and this time Boucher squeezes it wide of point
full down leg stump, Albie also moves away and flicks with it away for four, a shot of immense confidence and whats more, he's picked out the gap to ease the pressure
sweeps from outside off stump into the gap behind square leg

there she goes! Albie doesn't waste a second in sizing up Hauritz, who tosses it up from around the stumps, down he goes, clearing the front leg and depositing that into the second tier above midwicket, what a stunning hit
swings across the line again, miscuing this one up into the starry night, Marsh runs across from midwicket and dives in vain, just missing what would have been a blinder
swings again and pings the midwicket ropes, what fun he is
smartly fired in wider and Albie has a swing and a miss

one hit too many, trying to finish it off with a six, but he doesn't get the desired power on the slog and the ball is taken down at wide long-on by Hopes, running around and sliding onto his knees to complete a good catch
full outside off stump, he kneels down and drives to extra cover
fuller still, inviting the drive, but Botha watches it go to Haddin
too wide this time, wobbling away, Botha chases and misses
lovely shot off bent knee, Tait pitches full and wide and Botha gets to the pitch, driving a classy shot between the covers, and thats it for Australia as South Africa go up 2-1
